Description: Thanks for looking at this 2000 Fender ’72 Telecaster Thinline Reissue. It’s a made-in-Mexico version with natural body, pearloid pickguard and maple neck. It’s in very good condition. The neck has darkened a bit with time as you can see in the photos – the light amber color looks very cool, nicely vintage! It has one important improvement in the electronics: the original volume and tone pots were replaced with Mojotone 500k pots. These new pots deliver much better high-end articulation from the Fender humbucking pickups. These Mojotone pots are a huge improvement over the original, muddy-sounding 250k pots. (Sorry, I don’t have the original pots.) Otherwise, the guitar is totally stock. Unlike some of the more recent Mexican-made Tele Thinlines, this one is nicely light in weight – only 6 lbs 13oz. It’s super clean, but a couple of dings are shown in photos. One minor ding in lower body, near the cable jack. A couple of very minor impressions on the back of the neck. Otherwise, this guitar is remarkably clean for its age Sorry,it does not come with a case or gig bag, but it will be well packed for shipment.PayPal only. USA bids only please.
